Title: BARCELONA KICKS THE STARS OUT! MESSI is shocked by what's happening! BAR√áA'S REBUILDING HAS BEGUN!
Descripition:
BARCELONA KICKS THE STARS OUT! MESSI is shocked by what's happening! BAR√áA'S REBUILDING HAS BEGUN!

BARCELONA REBUILDING IS ABOUT TO BEGIN?
As; Marca

Many players can leave Barcelona during the summer transfer window. According to As, the president of the Catalan club, Joan Laporta, is planning a major rebuilding. Jordi Alba, Sergio Busquets, Sergi Roberto, Antoine Griezmann, Philippe Coutinho and Ousmane Dembele may leave the team. There is already an offer from Bayern to sign Busquets, according to As and the management may decide to sell him due to the difficult financial situation. Atletico Madrid is the main contender for Alba. Laporta wants to strengthen the center of defense - his plans include the signing of De Ligt and Pau Torres. Both transfers are difficult to pull off due to the high price tag of the players. Bar√ßa's main strategy for the summer is signing free agents + swap deals of players - according to this formula, the Catalans want to acquire De Ligt - an exchange for Griezmann is also possible. As a result, it turns out that Barca can sell Alba, Griezmann and Busquets. We wonder how Lionel Messi likes all that? Will he change his mind? Perhaps the Argentinean will be outraged and leave the club too? Joan Laporta seems to be playing with fire!

Well? Does it sound convincing? In general, we are waiting for the official information and the terms of the new contract.

Today we'll talk about why Messi made the decision to stay and why it deserves an immense amount of respect!

Title: Top 10 Solo Goals Specialists In Football 2019
Descripition:
Home of Football ‚û† Top 10 Solo Goals Specialist In Football 2019

We got an idea to make a video for best solo goals specialist and we chose 10 players who scored the most goals from 2012/13 season to current 2019 year. Like always, you need to know that we put 2019 year in the title because we chose only players who are still active in football, expect of Robben who was amazing solo goals specialist and finished his career this year. 

For these guys who can't understand what means 2019 year in the title!
Stats are provided from period of 2012/13 season to current 2019 year. 
Stats are based only on players who are active now in football and that's the reason why there is 2019 in the title.
We are searching for a player who is active in football in 2019 and who has scored the most solo goals from period of 2012/13 - 2019!
That's the point of the video! 

As you know, we can't use EPL content in the video. Riyad Mahrez is the only player on the list who scored only solo goals in EPL. So, that's why we put some random goals.

*Points - every solo goal is rated with the mark 1-5. 

Sometimes we're working 100+ hours to make video like this. Your feedback means us a lot, please leave a like and press that subscribe button if you enjoy in this video.

Title: Chelsea Road to Champions League Victory - 2021
Descripition:
Chelsea have been crowned Champions League winners for the first time in almost a decade after winning the 2020-21 final 1-0 against Manchester City in Porto.

This video depicts the amazing journey of chelsea from the group stages to winning the final

Thomas Tuchel's side found success repeatedly and hit Man City on the break in Porto to claim their first Champions League since Didier Drogba's heroics proved pivotal in Munich, against Bayern Munich, back in 2012. The two teams had only ever met in European competition once prior to tonight -- that being the semifinals of the 1970-71 UEFA European Cup Winners' Cup, which saw Chelsea win both legs 1-0.

By the end of the evening, it was the Blues who once again ran out the victors.

Title: Manchester City vs Chelsea: Champions League Final Preview | UCL on CBS Sports
Descripition:
The Champions League final will see two familiar foes square off yet again as Manchester City and Chelsea meet on May 29 in Istanbul. While they have never met in a UCL final as this is City's first ever appearance, they have played plenty just this season alone. While they normally just meet two times a season in the Premier League, they have already played twice this campaign and will play two more times before the season comes to an end. In fact, they will end up having played four times in five months by the end of May.

Title: THANK YOU, CRISTIANO RONALDO | Real Madrid Official Video
Descripition:
Real Madrid C. F. inform that, as per Cristiano Ronaldo's wishes and at his request, the club has allowed the player to complete his move to Juventus F. C.

Real Madrid would today like to place on record its thanks to a player who has shown himself to be the best in the world and made his mark on one of the greatest periods in our club's history and on the world game.

Apart from the titles he has lifted, the honours secured and the on-field achievements during these nine years, Cristiano Ronaldo has been a role model in terms of commitment, hard work, responsibility, talent and self-improvement.
 
He became Real Madrid's leading all-time goalscorer, having scored 451 goals in his 438 appearances. In total, he won 16 pieces of silverware, including four European Cup crowns, three of which came in successive years, with these four continental triumphs coming in the past five seasons. In terms of individual honours, as a Real Madrid player, he won the Ballon d'Or on four occasions, The Best award twice and claimed the Golden Shoe three times, amongst many other accolades.
 
Cristiano Ronaldo will forever be one of Real Madrid's biggest icons and will represent a unique figure for future generations.

Real Madrid will always be his home.

Cristiano Ronaldo dos Santos Aveiro (born 5 February 1985) is a Portuguese professional footballer who plays as a forward for Serie A club Juventus and captains the Portugal national team. He has won 30 major trophies in his career, including seven league titles, five UEFA Champions Leagues, one UEFA European Championship, and one UEFA Nations League title. Ronaldo holds the records for the most goals (130) and assists (41) in the history of the UEFA Champions League. He is one of the few recorded players to have made over 1,000 professional career appearances and has scored over 700 senior career goals for club and country. He is also the second player to score 100 international goals, and the first European to achieve the feat.

Title: Liverpool.com podcast: Summer Premier League transfer draft | Raphinha, Pedro Neto, Bissouma
Descripition:
As the transfer window gets underway and big-name players like Ibrahima Konate are beginning to move clubs, the Liverpool.com NFL-inspired draft returns.

Host Dan Morgan is joined by Joel Rabinowitz, debutant James Martin, and Blood Red's Matt Addison as they make their selections for who could make an impact for Liverpool from the bottom 12 Premier League clubs (including those who were promoted this season, and excluding those who were relegated).

Each writer gets to pick five signings of their choice, and each pick must not exceed a current Transfermarkt value of over ¬£50m.

Picks must include at least one defender, one midfielder and one forward and each pick must be unique, so once a player is selected, no other writer can take them, with no more than two players from one club selected.

Among the predictable picks are Raphinha, Pedro Neto and Yves Bissouma, while there are also some more left-field options who Michael Edwards could turn to as the draft unfolds.

Liverpool are not in the running to sign highly-rated Ghana teenager Abdul Fatawu Issahaku this summer.

Reports in Ghana over the weekend claimed the Reds had stolen a march in the race to snap up the 17-year-old attacking midfielder.

It was suggested Liverpool had swooped in to take the player from Ghanaian club Steadfast FC ahead of Bundesliga side Bayer Leverkusen.

However, the ECHO understands the Reds are not pursuing a deal for Issahaku at present.

1) Manchester United star Bruno Fernandes nominated for Premier League Player of the Year award

According to The Metro, Manchester United star Bruno Fernandes has been nominated for the Premier League Player of the Year award.

A total of eight players have been nominated. Apart from Kane and Fernandes, the others are Kevin de Bruyne, Ruben Bias, Mohamed Salah, Jack Grealish, Mason Mount and Tomas Soucek.


2) Manchester United manager Solskjaer nominated for Premier League Manager of the Year award

According to The Daily Mail, Manchester United manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer has been nominated for the Premier League Manager of the Year award.

Others in the fray include Manchester City boss Pep Guardiola, Leeds United‚Äôs Marcelo Bielsa, West Ham United‚Äôs David Moyes, and Leicester City‚Äôs Brendan Rodgers.


3) Man United ace Mason Greenwood pulls out of England squad for Euros due to injury

According to The Athletic, Manchester United star Mason Greenwood has withdrawn from the England squad ahead of this month‚Äôs European Championships.

It is the first time since being sent home from Iceland that the youngster was picked by Southgate. Unfortunately, it has now been cut short.


4) Jesse Lingard set for EURO 2020 heartbreak as Gareth Southgate swings the axe

Manchester United midfielder Jesse Lingard will not be included in Gareth Southgate‚Äôs final 26-man England squad, according to The Athletic‚Äòs David Ornstein.

Nobody would have thought Lingard would have been in the England picture for the Euros, had you asked them at the start of the 2020/21 campaign.


5) Manchester United set to pocket millions if Romelu Lukaku quits Inter Milan this summer

According to Manchester Evening News, Manchester United could be set to pocket millions if Romelu Lukaku decides to leave Italian champions Inter Milan this summer.

Regardless of where he ends up, United could end up enriching themselves.


6) Liverpool target intent on securing ¬£40M move to Manchester United

Atletico Madrid midfielder Saul Niguez is hoping to sign for Manchester United this summer, according to Todo Fichajes.

The Express have previously reported that Saul has a ¬£60M buyout clause, but Atletico would be prepared to do business if a bid in the region of ¬£40M was received.


7) Manchester United asked to fork out ‚Ç¨60m for Pedro Goncalves

According to the Portuguese outlet Record (h/t Sport Witness), Manchester United have been told what it will take for them to sign Sporting Lisbon star Pedro Goncalves.


8) Manchester United asked to pay at least ‚Ç¨65m to land Jules Kounde

According to Spanish outlet Diario de Sevilla (h/t Sport Witness), Sevilla have lowered the asking price for French defender Jules Kounde amidst Manchester United interest.

The Frenchman will however not come cheap and has a release clause of ‚Ç¨80million. Sevilla for their part are willing to take a hit and will accept around ‚Ç¨70m for Kounde.


9) Manchester United still in the fray for AC Milan star Hakan Calhanoglu

According to the Italian outlet TuttoMercatoWeb (h/t The Express), Manchester United have made an offer to Hakan Calhanoglu to join them in the upcoming summer transfer window.


10) Manchester United reach ‚Äòagreement in principle‚Äô ahead of completing Jadon Sancho transfer

Manchester United have an ‚Äòagreement in principle‚Äô with Borussia Dortmund‚Äôs Jadon Sancho, according to Bundesliga journalist Constantin Eckner.

Man United fans will be keeping their fingers tightly crossed that the 2021 summer transfer window is a busy one.


11) Manchester United handed a boost over PSG in Cristiano Ronaldo pursuit

According to The Athletic, Manchester United have received a major boost in their pursuit of Juventus ace Cristiano Ronaldo.

According to the report, a switch to the Parc des Princes appears unlikely. Whether this is the encouragement that United need in order to make their move remains to be seen.

Title: Manchester United Latest News 31 May 2021
Descripition:
Join this channel to get access to perks:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCC7pW8aiq_HfW0DTqZu-1Vg/join
Don't forget to subscribe üôèüôè
1) Alaves keen to keep Manchester United loanee Facundo Pellistri for the 2021/22 season

According to journalist Jonathan Shragar via Inside Futbol, Deportivo Alaves are keen to keep hold of Manchester United loanee Facundo Pellistri for another season.

The young Uruguayan arrived at Old Trafford on deadline day last summer. He impressed for the reserves before being permitted to leave the club on loan in January.


2) Ole Gunnar Solskjaer keen to keep Anthony Martial at Manchester United

According to the Daily Mail (h/t Express), Manchester United manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer has made his decision regarding the future of Anthony Martial at the club.

The Frenchman came into the 2020/21 season riding high on the wave of a spectacular 2019/20 season. He ended the season as United‚Äôs top scorer and was also voted the Manchester United Players‚Äô Player of the Year.


3) Manchester United star Diogo Dalot unsure of AC Milan return

According to Gazzetta Dello Sport (h/t Sport Witness), Manchester United star Diogo Dalot has admitted that he is unsure of what the future holds for him, with his loan spell at AC Milan ending.


4) Fabrizio Romano: Tom Heaton set for Manchester United medical

According to reliable journalist Fabrizio Romano on Twitter, Tom Heaton is set to undergo his medical at Manchester United in the coming weeks.

The 35-year-old goalkeeper is a former graduate of the United academy. He failed to make a single appearance for the Red Devils and left for greener pastures in 2010.


5) Manchester United to sanction four signings this summer

According to the Daily Mail (h/t Express), Manchester United have sanctioned four summer signings that Ole Gunnar Solskjaer can make in the upcoming summer transfer window.

The Red Devils go into the off-season following a disappointing end to the 2020/21 campaign. Certain deficiencies have been laid bare in our squad and will need immediate readdressing.


6) Saul Niguez keen to push through a move to Manchester United

According to the Mirror (h/t Express), Atletico Madrid midfielder Saul Niguez is all set to force through a transfer to Manchester United this summer.

The 26-year-old has been a key part of Diego Simeone‚Äôs stellar Atletico side the past few years. His role in the side has somewhat diminished this season, making him seek a new challenge elsewhere.


7) The future of Lautaro Martinez at Inter Milan remains unclear amidst Manchester United interest

Speaking to Italian television broadcaster Telelombardia (h/t Sempre Inter), football agent Alejandro Camano has opened up on the future of Inter Milan ace Lautaro Martinez who had earlier garnered interest from Manchester United.

The Argentine forward was on United‚Äôs radar last summer but a deal failed to materialize. A year on, interest appears to have cooled somewhat but the player continues to go from strength to strength.


8) Manchester United pick Jadon Sancho over Harry Kane

According to the Daily Mail, Manchester United have chosen to make their move for Jadon Sancho ahead of Tottenham Hotspur ace Harry Kane.

The Red Devils are keen to bring in a right-winger and have earmarked Jadon Sancho as their man. United have a long-term interest in the Borussia Dortmund star and unsuccessfully tried to sign him last summer.


9) Glazers in talks with Jorge Mendes to seal Cristiano Ronaldo deal

According to The Express, Manchester United owners Glazers have held talks with superagent Jorge Mendes regarding a move for Cristiano Ronaldo.

The 36-year-old, despite his age, remains one of the best players in world football. He led the Serie A scoring charts last season as Juventus ensured Champions League qualification on the final day.

A return to the Theatre of Dreams has been mooted ever since he left United. This summer, it looks to be a real possibility rather than just wishful talk.

Title: Ronaldo Wants Man Utd Move? Paul Pogba Signing Contract? Manchester United News
Descripition:
Cristiano Ronaldo has been reported by a sports journalist from The Athletic and friend of the channel Laurie Whitwell to be unsettled at Juventus. With a poor end to the season with Andrea Pirlo being sacked as head coach of Juventus and an impending Champions League ban for next season, Ronaldo is reportedly interested in a return to Old Trafford to play Champions League football next season. According to The Express, Atletico Madrid star Kieran Trippier has thrown a spanner on the chances of Manchester United landing him this summer.

According to transfer news from MEN, Manchester United could finally get a chance to sign Ben White. The Brighton defender could be let go as chairman Tony Bloom spoke about the club‚Äôs losses due to the pandemic.


3) Manchester United get boost in Jules Kounde pursuit

According to transfer news from Metro, Manchester United have received a boost in their pursuit of Jules Kounde. The Sevilla defender has claimed that he might be moving clubs in the summer to fulfil his ambitions.

Kounde is an extremely promising player who appears to have a bright future ahead of him. He was a part of the Sevilla side that knocked United out of the Europa League last season.


4) Manchester United tipped to sign Allan Saint-Maximin

According to transfer news from Chronicle Live, Manchester United have been named as one of the destinations Allan Saint-Maximin could head to. The Newcastle winger has been tipped to leave the club in the summer with the club needing cash.


5) Real Madrid ready to sell Manchester United target Raphael Varane

According to transfer news from Express, Real Madrid are ready to sell Raphael Varane who is a target for Manchester United. The Spanish side will cash in on the defender if he does not renew his contract with them.

According to transfer news from Metro, Jack Grealish has fuelled speculation regarding links to Manchester United. The Aston Villa captain liked a fan‚Äôs Tweet in which the fan was desperately asking the player to join United.

United were heavily linked with the player in recent windows. The Villa skipper is today one of the best midfielders in the league.

According to transfer news from Sky Sports, Manchester United appear to be the most likely destination for Jadon Sancho. Other Premier League sides such as Chelsea are also interested but it looks as if Sancho will head to United.

8) Manchester United to go after Harry Kane as Erling Haaland alternative

According to transfer news from Eurosport, Manchester United will turn their attention to Harry Kane, with Erling Haaland likely to stay back. The Borussia Dortmund forward is likely to remain at the club, which could see United go after Kane.

The 27-year-old has performed splendidly for Spurs for a number of seasons and is amongst the best strikers in world football.

According to transfer news from Express, Manchester United have received a boost in their pursuit of Cristiano Ronaldo. Juventus recently sacked Andrea Pirlo and re-appointed Max Allegri and the latter is not said to be a fan of Ronaldo.

The Portuguese superstar is one of the best players in the history of the game. Despite turning 36, Ronaldo continues to impress and has scored 29 goals in 33 Serie A appearances for Juventus in an underwhelming season.

McTominay & Fred have done fine jobs for Man Utd in midfield, but Solskjaer‚Äôs side have lacked a genuine holder in midfield to replace Nemanja Matic and the 22 year old would be the perfect man for the job.

Title: Reacting to MY 2020/21 Premier League Predictions
Descripition:
Welcome back guys! today we‚Äôre going to be Reviewing My 2020/21 Premier League Predictions. 

‚ñ∫ SUBSCRIBE to STATMAN DAVE: http://bit.ly/StatmanDaveYoutube 

First let‚Äôs start with the bottom of the table, earlier in the season I thought that Fulham had come up a season early and still had some building to do in the squad. Similar with West Brom who I didn‚Äôt think were ready for a challenge in the Premier League, having both sides being relegated. Although I was off the mark on the Aston Villa relegation, who continued their good form from the end of the 2019/20 season when they had to fight for their place in the Premier League. The additions of Emiliano Mart√≠nez and Matty Cash were huge for Dean Smith this season, as well as keeping Jack Grealish at the club last summer.

In terms of the middle of the table, I had Leeds finishing outside the top 10 - as much as I admire Marcelo Bielsa's work I felt that Leeds needed a season before breaking into the top 10. But after a strong end to the season, Bielsa‚Äôs men finished ahead of Everton and just behind Arsenal in 9th. 

‚ñ∫ CHECK US OUT ON TWITCH: http://bit.ly/SMDTwitch 

Moving to the top of the table, I predicted the right top 4, but just got it wrong on the title winners as I had Jurgen Klopp‚Äôs Liverpool lifting the title ahead of Man City. Liverpool did extremely well to finish in the top 4 and is something that I called when we did our most recent Top 4 prediction. Even though they lost their 3 starting centre backs, Liverpool conceded just 42 goals - the 4th best defensive record in the league.

‚ñ∫ JOIN PATREON: https://bit.ly/StatmanPatreon 

I didn‚Äôt think City‚Äôs summer signings would make the difference and at the time of recording, they didn‚Äôt as they‚Äôd only signed Nathan Ake and Ferran Torres. But the addition of Ruben Dias combined with Liverpool losing their defensive unit was a huge swing in balance and City capitalised.
They also had Ilkay Gundogan step up who was basically a new signing given the improved level that he played at.

I think if it were a normal season for Liverpool and with the summer signings, Man Utd would have finished 3rd. The signing of Alex Telles did give United a starting left back, it just turned out Luke Shaw needed the competition. Luke Shaw has really emerged as a top full back this season with only Trent Alexander-Arnold (74) creating more chances than the United man (69). Marcus Rashford & Bruno Fernandes continued their excellence, Mason Greenwood continued to develop and Edinson Cavani announced himself with an excellent debut campaign for a 34 year old, being directly involved in a goal every 88 minutes.

Statman Dave Clips ‚û° http://bit.ly/StatmanClips 

How did your predictions look at the end of the Premier League season? Drop in the comments below what were your hits and misses for this season‚Äôs PL predictions.

Title: Premier League Stadiums 2021/22
Descripition:
‚û°Ô∏è 3Retro: https://bit.ly/3retrofootball_

This is a video of all stadiums and teams for the 2021/22 English Premier League season ordered by the capacities of the grounds. You will learn all the teams and the name, capacity, and opening year of each of the 20 stadiums. There is an aerial and inside-the-ground photo for each stadium.

The Premier League is the top level of the English football league system. There are 20 teams competing in the league each season. Each team plays 38 matches. The top four teams qualify for the next season's Champions League, the 5th placed team qualifies for the Europa League, and the bottom three teams are relegated to the EFL Championship. The 2021/22 season will begin on 14 August 2021. Norwich City, Watford, and Brentford are the three newly-promoted sides. Manchester City are the defending champions, having won their fifth Premier League title in the previous season.

Title: Harry Kane wins the Premier League Golden Boot for the third time
Descripition:
‚ñ∫ Subscribe to Sky Sports News: http://bit.ly/SkySportsNewsSub

Tottenham striker Harry Kane has won the Premier League Golden Boot in what may be his final season with the club.

The England international scored the opening goal in Spurs' 4-2 win over Leicester City on the final day. The 27-year-old has now won the award in three seasons - 2015-16, 2016-17, 2020-21 - becoming only the third player to do so after Thierry Henry (4) and Alan Shearer (3).

Kane also won the playmaker award, given to the player for the most assists, after he led the way in that category with 14.

Title: Sergio Aguero signs off his Premier League career in style as Manchester City thrash Everton 5-0
Descripition:
‚ñ∫ Subscribe to Sky Sports News: http://bit.ly/SkySportsNewsSub

Sergio Aguero signed off from the Premier League in perfect style, scoring twice after coming on as a substitute as champions Man City finished with a 5-0 win over Everton, whose European dreams were ended with defeat at the Etihad Stadium

The moment every City fan wanted came in the 65th minute when Aguero, who will leave after 10 years at the club, replaced Riyad Mahrez, and it took him just six minutes to get on the scoresheet with a smart finish past Jordan Pickford.

He struck again five minutes later with a brilliant header, and he had a few more chances to add to his 260 City career goals, but he had to make do with a double as he ended his Premier League career in fairy-tale style.

Title: HIGHLIGHTS | Chelsea vs Arsenal (0-1) | Smith Rowe | Premier League
Descripition:
Emile Smith Rowe capitalised on a Chelsea mistake to score the only goal of the game, and extend our winning run in the league to three games.

Having scored his first ever Premier League goal at the weekend against West Brom,  he netted again in the derby to set us on the way to a hard-earned three points.

This goal owed a bit more to good fortune though, as he stroked home from Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang's pass, once Chelsea keeper Kepa Arrizabalaga had scrambled back to prevent an own goal.

For much of the rest of the game it was about resolute defending, right from the front back to our five-man defence.

That was the system Mikel Arteta went for from the start, but it was the most central of those three centre backs - Pablo Mari - who was caught in possession early on to gift Chelsea the first chance of the game. Kai Havertz nicked the ball off the Spaniards toes to race away on goal, but he blazed over when one-on-one.

It was Chelsea's turn to hand out the gifts next though, and it led to Smith Rowe scoring the only goal of the game.

Jorginho's wayward backpass put Kepa in difficulty. The keeper managed to palm away from his own goalline, but Aubameyang was lurking to pull the loose ball back to Smith Rowe in front of goal, and his low shot squirmed in off the post.

Rob Holding made a superb close-range block from Mason Mount's shot to keep us ahead, but Chelsea kept knocking on the door for the remainder of the half, drawing two smart stops from Bernd Leno.

The hosts continued to pin us back at the start of the second half, and we had to remain organised in and around our own penalty box.

Christian Pulisic did have the ball in the net, but the goal was disallowed for a clear offside after VAR intervened.

Hector Bellerin was introduced and immediately had a sight of goal, but shot tamely after good build up play involving Martin Odegaard.

We were certainly coming out of our shells as an attacking threat now, with Odegaard himself blazing over from a promising position.

Chelsea - three days before their FA Cup final appointment with Leicester City - piled forward late on and hit the woodwork twice in succession in injury time.

But we were rewarded for an excellent defensive effort with a 1-0 win, securing our first double over Chelsea since 2003/04.

Title: Carlo Ancelotti leaves Everton to re-join Real Madrid

‚ñ∫ Subscribe to Sky Sports News: http://bit.ly/SkySportsNewsSub

Carlo Ancelotti has left his role as Everton manager to take up the position of head coach at Real Madrid.
